### Problem Description

While experimenting with multivalued fields and `null` values in ES|QL, I found that `null` values are stripped out and only non-null values are kept.

Digging further, I found that the likely cause is because `null` values aren't stored in docvalues. 

Is this expected, at least in ES|QL?

### Steps to Reproduce

In the Kibana dev console, ingest some test data:
```
POST /test_array/_bulk
{ "index": { "_id": "123" }}
{ "x": [1, 2, 3] }
{ "index": { "_id": "12n" }}
{ "x": [1, 2, null] }
{ "index": { "_id": "1n3" }}
{ "x": [1, null, 3] }
{ "index": { "_id": "n23" }}
{ "x": [null, 2, 3] }
{ "index": { "_id": "nnn" }}
{ "x": [null, null, null] }
{ "index": { "_id": "n" }}
{ "x": null }
```

Run this ES|QL query:
```
POST _query
{
  "query": "FROM test_array METADATA _id | KEEP _id, x | LIMIT 1000",
  "columnar": false
}
```

The result, reformatted for readability:
```
{
  "columns": [
    { "name": "_id", "type": "keyword" },
    { "name": "x", "type": "long" }
  ],
  "values": [
    [ "123", [ 1, 2, 3 ]],
    [ "12n", [ 1, 2 ]],
    [ "1n3", [ 1, 3 ]],
    [ "n23", [ 2, 3 ]],
    [ "nnn", null ],
    [ "n", null ]
  ]
}
```

We can see that all `null` values have been removed, and that fields containing only `null` values have been replaced by a single `null`.


The same is visible when requesting docvalues in `_search`: `null` values are present in `source`, but not in `fields`.

```
GET test_array/_search
{
  "docvalue_fields": ["x"]
}
```
